               <head>Notice on Surat &amp; Autobiography of a Balochi Leader, 2 works</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064912">
                  <summary>Collection of two unrelated prose works: 1) a notice on Surat; 2) an autobiography of a Balochi leader</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115302 http://lccn.loc.gov/n80138245" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3817-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="23r">ff. 1v-23r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled concise account on the political and military history of the port city of Surat, based on historical sources (for example, the Ṭabaqāt-i Akbarī and the Tārīkh-i Firishtah)</p>
                        <p>The account extends from the period before the Islamic kingdoms to the port's take over by the British East India Company, on 30 Rajab 1174/7 March 1761</p>
                        <p>Author not mentioned </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 23r): completed Wednesday, salkh (=30) Shaʿbān 1213/6 February 1799 </p>
                        <p>Original folio count (23) below colophon date, written in words and figures in reverse</p>
                        <p>IOL stamp: 24 Jun. 1912</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85011394 http://lccn.loc.gov/n86066493 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85010050" n="2" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3817-item2">
                     <locus from="24v" to="85v">ff. 24v-85v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7151">Ḥājjī Shīr Khān</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7151">حاجى شير خان</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled autobiographical account by the eighteenth-century Baluchi leader, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7151" ref="Persian_0146" role="aut">Ḥājjī Shīr Khān ibn Amīr Ḥasan Khān ibn Amīr Murād ibn Amīr Dūstan Khān ibn Mīr Badr al-Din Khān</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>The text runs intermittently, interrupted by lacunae, in the sequence: ff. 24v-47v, 48v-68v, 72v-81r, 81v-85v</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
